MANULIFE COMPLIANCE GUIDELINES FOR FINANCIAL ADVISORS

DATA PROTECTION:
- Client personal data must not be shared outside of Manulife systems.
- All client conversations must be logged within 24 hours.
- Client consent is required before sharing data with third parties.
- Data retention: Client records must be kept for 7 years after policy termination.
- Digital communications with clients must use Manulife-approved platforms only.

SALES PRACTICES:
- Advisors must complete a needs analysis before recommending any product.
- All product recommendations must be documented with reasoning.
- "Best interest" duty: recommend what suits the client, not what pays the highest commission.
- Cool-off period: clients have 21 days to cancel a new policy for a full refund.
- Advisors must disclose all fees, charges, and commission structures to the client.
- Replacements: When recommending a client replace an existing policy, a replacement analysis form must be completed.

COMMUNICATION:
- All client-facing materials must use approved Manulife templates.
- Social media posts about products must be pre-approved by compliance.
- Claims of guaranteed returns are strictly prohibited.
- WhatsApp/WeChat may be used for scheduling only, not for policy advice.
- Email signatures must include full name, license number, and Manulife disclaimer.
- All promotional materials must include risk warnings where applicable.

ANTI-MONEY LAUNDERING:
- Verify client identity for all new policies using valid government-issued ID.
- Flag any single premium payment above HKD 500,000 for review.
- Report suspicious transaction patterns to compliance@manulife.com.
- Cash payments above HKD 120,000 require additional documentation.
- Politically Exposed Persons (PEP) checks must be performed for all new clients.

COMPLAINT HANDLING:
- All complaints must be acknowledged within 2 business days.
- Written response must be provided within 14 business days.
- Complaints must be logged in the central complaint management system.
- Escalate unresolved complaints to the Compliance Manager after 30 days.

CONTINUING PROFESSIONAL DEVELOPMENT:
- Advisors must complete a minimum of 15 CPD hours per year.
- At least 3 hours must be on compliance and ethics topics.
- Records of CPD activities must be maintained and submitted annually.
